<HL>
   Hourly Wages Rose in Italy
</HL>
<DATE>
07/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   ROME -- Hourly wages in Italy rose an average of 3% in May
from April and were up 7.8% from a year earlier, the state
statistics bureau Istat said.
   Istat attributed the sharp monthly increase to the
automatic indexation for inflation in all wages covered by
collective bargaining procedures.
